-I see.

32
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,733
So you've been out looking
for a bride all this time?

33
00:03:03,066 --> 00:03:06,500
-You're the only person
who's even been nice to me.

34
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,733
That's right.

35
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:11,666
I should grant you a
wish for saving my life.

36
00:03:11,766 --> 00:03:12,733
-Grant me a wish?

37
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:16,200
But I don't have
anything I-- wait.

38
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,333
What kind of wish?

39
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:18,666
[bell ringing]

40
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:20,400
[laughter]

41
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,600
-I am not your
ordinary ghost cat.

42
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,566
In fact, perhaps
you've heard of me.

43
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:30,800
I am the famous Maomolin,
legendary 3,000 year old

44
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:35,433
Chinese ghost cat who carried
a bell to search for his bride.

45
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:38,266
Make whatever wish you want.

46
00:03:38,366 --> 00:03:41,266
Do you have a girl you like?

47
00:03:41,366 --> 00:03:41,807
-Oh.

48
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,100
Of course I do.

49
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,200
MAOMOLIN: Your girlfriend?

50
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,500
-Not yet.

51
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,333
MAOMOLIN: You haven't proposed?

52
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,300
-Don't be dumb.

53
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,500
