66
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:16,607
-OK.

67
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:17,133
OK.

68
00:04:17,233 --> 00:04:17,674
Jeez.

69
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,233
-I can handle my own problems.

70
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:24,633
I saved your life
because I wanted to.

71
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,800
You don't have to
thank me for it.

72
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:30,566
Besides, how's some dumb
cat supposed to help me?

73
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,400
-But I'm a guy, too.

74
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,800
I can't just ignore the
fact that you saved me.

75
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,600
I have to repay the debt.

76
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,566
Ready or not.

77
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,066
Here I come.

78
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:47,000
[groan]

79
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,966
[music playing]

80
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:53,933
[bell ringing]

81
00:05:03,466 --> 00:05:04,300
WOMAN: Akane?

82
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,433
Another package from Ryoga.

83
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:07,100
AKANE: Coming.

84
00:05:08,566 --> 00:05:09,166
-Oh, well.

85
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:10,000
Golly.

86
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,866
Isn't he the considerate one.

87
00:05:11,966 --> 00:05:13,333
I sure hope you're grateful.

88
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:15,333
-Your jealousy is showing.

89
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:15,966
-It what?

90
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,366
-Gee.

91
00:05:18,466 --> 00:05:20,400
I wonder where he's
traveling this time.

92
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,700
RYOGA (VOICEOVER): Dear Akane.

93
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,733
Just a note to let you know
I'll be dropping by soon.

94
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:27,466
I need to ask you
something important.

95
00:05:27,566 --> 00:05:28,266
-Huh.

96
00:05:28,366 --> 00:05:29,666
I wonder what that could be.

97
00:05:29,766 --> 00:05:31,500
RANMA: So what did
he send you, anyway?

98
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,400
-Hm.

99
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,000
Good question.

100
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:36,300
Hm.

101
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,000
-What the heck?

102
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:40,666
AKANE: Dried fish and cat food?

103
00:05:40,766 --> 00:05:42,566
[music playing]

104
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:45,000
[heavy breathing]

105
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:48,166
-That's weird.

106
00:05:48,266 --> 00:05:49,466
How did I end up here?

107
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:53,700
(SHOUTING) Where am I now?

108
00:05:55,266 --> 00:05:58,133
[music playing]

109
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,933
[thunder]

110
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:22,100
[growling and barking]

111
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,966
[bells ringing]

112
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:33,133
-Let's see.

113
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:36,233
Ryoga's about a week
late, meaning that he's--

114
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:38,233
-Practically on time.

115
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:39,733
-I hate it when the
sky's like this.

116
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:40,533
-Me too.

117
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:42,400
Let's hurry home.

118
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,433
RYOGA: Can I ask you a question?

119
00:06:46,566 --> 00:06:47,600
-Hey, look.

120
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:49,033
If it isn't Ryoga.

121
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:53,700
-Th-- this is the town where
Akane Tendo lives, isn't it?

122
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,500
-Huh.

123
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,933
That's a weird thing to say.

124
00:06:56,033 --> 00:06:58,866
Well, as a matter of fact,
she's right over there.

125
00:06:58,966 --> 00:06:59,407
-Huh?

126
00:07:01,566 --> 00:07:02,766
-Now you're being ridiculous.

127
00:07:03,966 --> 00:07:05,566
MAOMOLIN (VOICEOVER):
There's that Ranma.

128
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:08,100
He's got Shampoo and Akane.

129
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,466
Why I ought to--

130
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,233
-Hey, you guys.

131
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,300
Looks like Ryoga's back in town.

132
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:15,866
Bye.

133
00:07:15,966 --> 00:07:17,333
-See you, dude.

134
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:18,133
-Oh, Ryoga.

135
00:07:18,233 --> 00:07:18,966
-Hey, man.

136
00:07:19,066 --> 00:07:20,000
How's it going?

137
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:21,966
-Ranma.

138
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:23,300
What's wrong?

139
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,333
-Nothing that I can--

140
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:28,566
-We were just on our way home,
so do you want to come along?

141
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:29,600
-I'd love to.

142
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,600
AKANE: Ranma, come on.

143
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,200
We're leaving.

144
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,441
-Coming.

145
00:07:35,766 --> 00:07:38,100
[thunder]

146
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:43,033
[suspenseful music playing]

147
00:07:46,566 --> 00:07:49,066
-Don't you think he's
acting kind of weird?

148
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:51,466
-Well, he seems kind
of the same to me.

149
00:07:51,566 --> 00:07:53,366
-He's like a different person.

150
00:07:53,466 --> 00:07:56,200
-So he's probably just
tired from his trip.

151
00:07:56,300 --> 00:08:00,266
So, how was your-- there he is.

152
00:08:00,366 --> 00:08:00,833
Hey, slowpoke.

153
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:01,833
Hurry up.

154
00:08:01,933 --> 00:08:03,833
[thunder]

155
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:05,466
-I guess he's the same.

156
00:08:05,566 --> 00:08:06,700
AKANE: I'm home.

157
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,133
KASUMI: Welcome back.

158
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:08,966
Ryoga, hello.

159
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,133
I was just finishing up dinner.

160
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:13,933
We'd love to have you over.

161
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:15,133
Hm.

162
00:08:15,233 --> 00:08:17,500
Akane, would you mind
helping me in the kitchen?

163
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,766
-Sure.

164
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,166
We'll talk later, OK?

165
00:08:20,266 --> 00:08:21,266
So don't go anywhere.

166
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:23,941
-I won't.

167
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:28,074
-Got you.

168
00:08:30,266 --> 00:08:31,866
[spring sound]

169
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,566
MAOMOLIN (VOICEOVER):
You can do it.

170
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:37,500
Pretend you didn't see it.

171
00:08:39,066 --> 00:08:42,333
I can't stand it anymore.

172
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:42,874
No.

173
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,800
-Kasumi says dinner's
almost ready, so--

174
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,766
[meowing]

175
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,466
Thank you, Kasumi.

176
00:08:55,566 --> 00:08:57,333
[eating sounds]

177
00:09:07,366 --> 00:09:08,433
-Would you like to eat mine?

178
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:12,433
-I'd love to, but only
if you don't mind.

179
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,300
Fish is my favorite.

180
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:18,500
-I don't remember him
liking fish that much.

181
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,666
-Now do you believe me?

182
00:09:20,766 --> 00:09:22,433
-Can I have some more, please?

183
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:22,966
-Of course.

184
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:28,866
-Could you maybe mash it all up
in a bowl with some extra fish?

185
00:09:28,966 --> 00:09:29,833
-How funny.

186
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,733
That's just how
kitties like to eat.

187
00:09:34,966 --> 00:09:36,866
RYOGA: That was so good.

188
00:09:36,966 --> 00:09:38,566
KASUMI: I'm glad you enjoyed it.

189
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:40,466
Would you like
some nice hot tea?

190
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:42,533
-I'm sorry.

191
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,800
But I don't like tea very much.

192
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,600
Could I have some milk instead?

193
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:47,833
[spit]

194
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,333
-I always get so
tired after I eat.

195
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:56,066
Can I take a nap?

196
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:59,033
[purring snore]

197
