AKANE (VOICEOVER): Ry-- Ryoga?

222
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,566
[meow]

223
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:11,000
[music playing]

224
00:11:20,466 --> 00:11:22,833
[meowing]

225
00:11:26,581 --> 00:11:27,947
-Uh.

226
00:11:28,047 --> 00:11:30,414
[meowing]

227
00:11:31,447 --> 00:11:32,547
RYOGA (VOICEOVER):
Marry me, Akane.

228
00:11:34,181 --> 00:11:37,147
AKANE (VOICEOVER): When he said
that to me, was he serious?

229
00:11:39,714 --> 00:11:40,581
[sigh]

230
00:11:42,147 --> 00:11:44,981
[meowing and snoring]

231
00:11:49,514 --> 00:11:52,114
-I can't sleep with them
dumb cats out there.

232
00:11:52,214 --> 00:11:54,581
(SHOUTING) Would
you shut up, please?

233
00:11:54,681 --> 00:11:57,081
[loud meowing]

234
00:12:08,514 --> 00:12:09,814
[music playing]

235
00:12:09,914 --> 00:12:10,614
KASUMI: Akane.

236
00:12:10,714 --> 00:12:13,347
Hurry up, or you'll be late.

237
00:12:13,447 --> 00:12:13,888
-Coming.

238
00:12:16,614 --> 00:12:17,381
-Good morning, Akane.

239
00:12:19,214 --> 00:12:19,781
-Morning, Ryoga.

240
00:12:21,114 --> 00:12:23,647
-You're even prettier in
the morning, you know that?

241
00:12:24,981 --> 00:12:27,881
You don't mind if I stay
here a while, do you?

242
00:12:30,214 --> 00:12:34,081
-I'm, uh-- kind of in a hurry.

243
00:12:34,181 --> 00:12:34,847
Excuse me.

244
00:12:38,847 --> 00:12:40,747
-She must be nervous.

245
00:12:40,847 --> 00:12:43,247
[music playing]

246
00:12:45,214 --> 00:12:45,881
-Ranma.

247
00:12:45,981 --> 00:12:47,447
He was even weirder today.

248
00:12:47,547 --> 00:12:49,514
-I thought girls liked
being proposed to.

249
00:12:49,614 --> 00:12:51,514
-Be serious, will you?

250
00:12:51,614 --> 00:12:52,447
Aren't you worried?

251
00:12:53,781 --> 00:12:55,747
RANMA: What, that
you'll pick him over me?

252
00:12:57,347 --> 00:12:58,781
AKANE: I'm worried
about Ryoga, OK?

253
00:12:58,881 --> 00:13:00,247
He's totally different.

254
00:13:00,347 --> 00:13:02,247
What if something's wrong?

255
00:13:02,347 --> 00:13:03,281
RANMA: Oh.

256
00:13:03,381 --> 00:13:05,347
So you didn't like
his proposal, then.

257
00:13:05,447 --> 00:13:07,347
-That's not what I mean.

258
00:13:07,447 --> 00:13:08,714
RANMA: So what do you mean?

259
00:13:08,814 --> 00:13:09,681
-(SHOUTING) Never mind.

260
00:13:09,781 --> 00:13:11,147
[crash]

261
00:13:11,247 --> 00:13:12,581
[groan]

262
00:13:12,681 --> 00:13:16,014
[music playing]

263
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:21,547
TEACHER: So therefore
what we get is this.

264
00:13:21,647 --> 00:13:26,214
Which you use to get this,
thereby completing the equation

265
00:13:26,314 --> 00:13:27,547
and finishing the problem.

266
00:13:27,647 --> 00:13:30,014
RANMA (VOICEOVER): I thought
girls liked being proposed to.

267
00:13:32,047 --> 00:13:34,881
[snoring]

268
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:37,314
AKANE (VOICEOVER): Like
he's such a big expert.

269
00:13:37,414 --> 00:13:39,647
I'll bet he's just jealous.

270
