[crash]

272
00:13:41,881 --> 00:13:43,047
TEACHER: Go stand in the hall.

273
00:13:47,147 --> 00:13:48,447
-Stupid teacher.

274
00:13:48,547 --> 00:13:52,814
I wouldn't have fallen asleep if
it weren't for them dumb cats.

275
00:13:52,914 --> 00:13:56,314
[birds chirping]

276
00:13:56,414 --> 00:13:58,814
[purring sound]

277
00:13:58,914 --> 00:14:00,314
[wings flapping]

278
00:14:00,414 --> 00:14:03,314
[bells ringing]

279
00:14:05,914 --> 00:14:08,281
[wedding march playing]

280
00:14:10,881 --> 00:14:13,281
-Know what, darling?

281
00:14:13,381 --> 00:14:14,781
-Yes, precious?

282
00:14:14,881 --> 00:14:17,281
-I'm so happy, I could just cry.

283
00:14:18,881 --> 00:14:21,581
-But not as half as much as me.

284
00:14:21,681 --> 00:14:23,614
Give me some sugar, baby.

285
00:14:27,914 --> 00:14:30,247
-I'm so happy, Akane.

286
00:14:30,347 --> 00:14:31,414
[gasp]

287
00:14:34,814 --> 00:14:36,281
-Only a dream.

288
00:14:36,381 --> 00:14:38,281
[gasp]

289
00:14:38,381 --> 00:14:39,747
MAOMOLIN (VOICEOVER):
That's right.

290
00:14:39,847 --> 00:14:42,681
If I can get him
married to Akane,

291
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:46,914
then that would mean that
he would-- that we would--

292
00:14:47,014 --> 00:14:48,447
that I would--

293
00:14:48,547 --> 00:14:52,381
(SHOUTING) Finally be able to
stop searching for a bride.

294
00:14:52,481 --> 00:14:53,881
[wings flapping]

295
00:14:53,981 --> 00:14:56,347
[bells ringing]

296
00:14:57,947 --> 00:15:00,314
[wedding march playing]

297
00:15:04,214 --> 00:15:05,414
-If it isn't Ranma.

298
00:15:08,981 --> 00:15:09,881
-A-- Akane.

299
00:15:12,981 --> 00:15:14,281
-Gee whiz, Ranma.

300
00:15:14,381 --> 00:15:16,247
After Akane and
I became engaged,

301
00:15:16,347 --> 00:15:18,681
we stopped seen you around.

302
00:15:18,781 --> 00:15:20,881
Why was that, do you think?

303
00:15:20,981 --> 00:15:23,714
Well, you do realize you're
welcome to come back and visit,

304
00:15:23,814 --> 00:15:24,881
don't you?

305
00:15:24,981 --> 00:15:28,147
We could always use
company at the Tendo Dojo.

306
00:15:28,247 --> 00:15:30,014
Bye, bye, Ranma.

307
00:15:30,114 --> 00:15:31,381
Take care now, you hear?

308
00:15:31,481 --> 00:15:32,314
-Akane.

309
00:15:32,414 --> 00:15:34,914
Please don't leave me.

310
00:15:35,014 --> 00:15:36,314
[splash]

311
00:15:38,247 --> 00:15:40,247
-Oh, what an awful dream.

312
00:15:40,347 --> 00:15:41,014
Uh oh.

313
00:15:42,547 --> 00:15:43,281
-Saotome?

314
00:15:43,381 --> 00:15:43,870
Huh?

315
00:15:45,081 --> 00:15:45,522
Huh?

316
00:15:47,547 --> 00:15:49,914
[bells ringing]

317
00:15:51,981 --> 00:15:55,314
[music playing]

318
00:16:09,647 --> 00:16:10,114
RANMA: Akane?

319
00:16:10,214 --> 00:16:11,081
[gasp]

320
00:16:11,181 --> 00:16:11,622
-Ranma.

321
00:16:14,181 --> 00:16:15,314
-Are you thinking about Ryoga?

322
00:16:17,281 --> 00:16:18,881
Well, I know I am.

323
00:16:18,981 --> 00:16:20,981
What are you going to do?

324
00:16:21,081 --> 00:16:22,614
-I-- I don't know.

325
00:16:23,814 --> 00:16:27,181
-Yeah, well, whatever
you decide, Akane, it's

326
00:16:27,281 --> 00:16:30,114
got nothing to do
with me, right?

327
00:16:30,214 --> 00:16:35,081
If you could, though,
I'd ask that you--

328
00:16:35,181 --> 00:16:36,947
-That I what?

329
00:16:38,881 --> 00:16:39,322
-Uh.

330
00:16:41,114 --> 00:16:41,555
GIRL: Akane.

331
00:16:41,614 --> 00:16:42,347
[gasp]

332
00:16:42,447 --> 00:16:42,914
GIRL: Look.

333
00:16:43,014 --> 00:16:43,581
We've got lunch.

334
00:16:45,181 --> 00:16:46,781
-You didn't have to--

335
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:49,147
-Wasn't there someone
here just a minute ago?

336
00:16:49,247 --> 00:16:50,114
-No.

337
00:16:50,214 --> 00:16:51,414
I mean, uh, I'm alone.

338
00:16:51,514 --> 00:16:52,047
-You sure?

339
00:16:53,414 --> 00:16:54,214
-Come on, you guys.

340
00:16:54,314 --> 00:16:56,747
Are we going to eat or what?

341
00:16:56,847 --> 00:16:58,081
RANMA (VOICEOVER): Oh, great.

342
00:16:58,181 --> 00:17:00,914
I'm so tired, I forgot to eat.

343
00:17:01,014 --> 00:17:09,581
And I'm so weak, I can
barely-- got to let go.

344
00:17:12,181 --> 00:17:13,547
-Getting tricky, eh?

345
00:17:16,314 --> 00:17:18,647
-Poor Akane's
daddy, is him tired?

346
00:17:20,481 --> 00:17:22,147
SOUN: Excuse me, hello?

347
00:17:24,181 --> 00:17:25,547
I'm Akane's daddy.

348
00:17:29,181 --> 00:17:30,481
Mm.

349
00:17:30,581 --> 00:17:32,014
Feels good.

350
00:17:32,114 --> 00:17:33,214
-You need to relax.

351
00:17:33,314 --> 00:17:34,914
[bell ringing]

352
00:17:37,414 --> 00:17:39,447
[meowing]

353
00:17:39,547 --> 00:17:43,914
-Just as I was making progress,
that bicycle bell rang and--

354
00:17:47,014 --> 00:17:50,214
-Can someone tell
me how I got here?

355
00:17:50,314 --> 00:17:53,681
[music playing]

356
00:17:55,281 --> 00:17:56,181
SOUN: Hello.

357
00:17:56,281 --> 00:17:56,722
Hello.

358
00:17:56,781 --> 00:17:57,647
You OK?

359
00:17:57,747 --> 00:17:58,647
Ryoga.

360
00:17:58,747 --> 00:18:00,647
AKANE: I'm home.

361
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:01,188
-Ah.

362
00:18:03,714 --> 00:18:04,614
Akane.

363
00:18:04,714 --> 00:18:06,614
Be my bride.

364
00:18:06,714 --> 00:18:07,947
-But Ryoga, I--

365
00:18:08,047 --> 00:18:10,414
[scream]

366
00:18:10,514 --> 00:18:11,247
-Huh?

367
00:18:11,347 --> 00:18:11,788
Akane.

368
00:18:12,914 --> 00:18:13,647
Ryoga.

369
00:18:13,747 --> 00:18:14,881
What do you think you're doing?

370
00:18:16,314 --> 00:18:19,514
-You mind your own business,
or you're going to be sorry.

371
00:18:19,614 --> 00:18:21,314
[growl]

372
00:18:21,414 --> 00:18:22,447
-Ryoga.

373
00:18:22,547 --> 00:18:23,847
[crash]

374
00:18:23,947 --> 00:18:25,214
[cry]

375
00:18:26,447 --> 00:18:28,347
RANMA (VOICEOVER): That
shouldn't have happened.

376
00:18:28,447 --> 00:18:30,181
Ryoga's much tougher than that.

377
00:18:30,281 --> 00:18:32,347
It's like he's a
whole other per--

378
00:18:32,447 --> 00:18:34,781
[mystical sounds]

379
00:18:37,814 --> 00:18:40,147
-Thanks for nothing,
you big bully.

380
00:18:40,247 --> 00:18:42,581
You nearly knocked me right out.

381
00:18:42,681 --> 00:18:43,547
-Oh, no.

382
00:18:43,647 --> 00:18:44,614
Not you again.

383
00:18:46,547 --> 00:18:47,414
-The ghost cat.

384
00:18:47,514 --> 00:18:48,847
I should have known.

385
00:18:48,947 --> 00:18:51,914
-So he was in Ryoga
the whole time.

386
00:18:52,014 --> 00:18:52,581
-Yep.

387
00:18:52,681 --> 00:18:54,047
I she sure was.

388
00:18:54,147 --> 00:18:57,247
I was hoping you wouldn't
notice, but since you have,

389
00:18:57,347 --> 00:18:59,814
I'm hoping you'll be
able to forgive me.

390
00:19:01,081 --> 00:19:02,347
[groan]

391
00:19:02,447 --> 00:19:03,747
-Oh, my head.

392
00:19:03,847 --> 00:19:05,481
-I-- I-- I get it.

393
00:19:05,581 --> 00:19:08,147
So that's why you didn't want to
eat nothing but-- but cat food,

394
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:08,914
right?

395
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:10,281
-Huh?

396
00:19:10,381 --> 00:19:12,447
-Not to mention running
around on all fours

397
00:19:12,547 --> 00:19:14,647
and curling into
a ball to sleep.

398
00:19:14,747 --> 00:19:15,847
-Sure.

399
00:19:15,947 --> 00:19:18,181
And why he'd rather use
sand instead of a toilet.

400
00:19:20,047 --> 00:19:21,247
-Uh, yeah, man.

401
00:19:21,347 --> 00:19:24,147
So, uh, so-- so don't worry
about trying to kiss Akane

402
00:19:24,247 --> 00:19:25,981
and-- and proposing, and junk.

403
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,747
Because that was
the cat and not you.

404
00:19:29,314 --> 00:19:31,181
-I feel faint.

405
00:19:31,281 --> 00:19:33,814
-I was only trying
to do you a favor.

406
00:19:36,314 --> 00:19:38,581
-Embarrassing me like
that in front of everyone.

407
00:19:39,914 --> 00:19:41,147
Why I ought to--

408
00:19:41,247 --> 00:19:43,381
-You never would have been
able to propose without me.

409
00:19:45,247 --> 00:19:45,914
-Shut up.

410
00:19:46,014 --> 00:19:46,581
-OK, then.

411
00:19:46,681 --> 00:19:47,614
How about your feelings?

412
00:19:47,714 --> 00:19:50,247
You could never have
confessed to Akane

413
00:19:50,347 --> 00:19:52,681
if it hadn't been for
me, isn't that right?

414
00:19:54,181 --> 00:19:55,481
[punch]

415
00:19:55,581 --> 00:19:56,847
-Why you little--

416
00:19:56,947 --> 00:20:00,214
-When you kissed her, it was
your lips on Akane, not mine.

417
00:20:01,781 --> 00:20:02,681
[punch]

418
00:20:02,781 --> 00:20:03,681
-Quit it.

419
00:20:03,781 --> 00:20:05,047
-Just think about
how great it would

420
00:20:05,147 --> 00:20:07,447
be if you were to
team up with me.

421
00:20:07,547 --> 00:20:08,481
[punch]

422
00:20:08,581 --> 00:20:11,447
-Why won't you admit
that you need me?

423
00:20:11,547 --> 00:20:12,647
[punch]

424
00:20:12,747 --> 00:20:15,014
-You provide the body and
I provide the willpower.

425
00:20:15,114 --> 00:20:16,414
[punch]

426
00:20:16,514 --> 00:20:18,414
-Maybe I'll propose myself.

427
00:20:18,514 --> 00:20:20,247
(SHOUTING) Be my bride.

428
00:20:23,247 --> 00:20:26,781
-When I do propose,
I'll do it myself.

429
00:20:28,781 --> 00:20:30,614
[maomolin crying]

430
00:20:32,614 --> 00:20:34,914
[heavy breathing]

431
00:20:36,947 --> 00:20:37,647
-I got to go.

432
00:20:38,681 --> 00:20:39,122
-Ryoga.

433
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:43,314
[music playing]

434
00:20:43,414 --> 00:20:45,147
RYOGA (VOICEOVER): Oh, Akane.

435
00:20:45,247 --> 00:20:49,314
Maybe I can't say it
now, but someday, I

436
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:53,781
promise that I am-- uh oh.

437
00:20:53,881 --> 00:20:56,181
[rabbit call]

438
00:21:05,014 --> 00:21:06,381
[birds chirping]

439
00:21:06,481 --> 00:21:07,514
AKANE: OK, we're off.

440
00:21:09,014 --> 00:21:11,081
Aren't you wondering
where that ghost cat is?

441
00:21:12,514 --> 00:21:15,614
-If I never saw him again,
it would be too soon.

442
00:21:15,714 --> 00:21:17,381
Speaking of which,
we're going to be late.

443
00:21:19,847 --> 00:21:21,714
[meowing]

444
00:21:21,814 --> 00:21:24,114
RANMA: I knew it.

445
00:21:24,214 --> 00:21:27,314
MAOMOLIN: Wouldn't you like
one of my little bells?

446
00:21:27,414 --> 00:21:28,014
-Look.

447
00:21:28,114 --> 00:21:29,814
He's opened up a store.

448
00:21:29,914 --> 00:21:30,947
-Oh, man.

449
00:21:31,047 --> 00:21:32,414
I hate cats.

450
00:21:32,514 --> 00:21:35,314
-You won't get rid
of me that easy.

451
00:21:35,414 --> 00:21:37,781
Won't you be my bride?

452
00:21:43,814 --> 00:21:47,181
[music playing]

453
00:23:16,235 --> 00:23:17,102
NARRATOR: Come on, dad.

454
00:23:17,202 --> 00:23:18,535
Fighting over a game?

455
00:23:18,635 --> 00:23:19,202
What?

456
00:23:19,302 --> 00:23:19,902
Mr. Saotome's gone?

457
00:23:21,135 --> 00:23:21,735
Really?

458
00:23:21,835 --> 00:23:22,702
He's joined the circus?

459
00:23:23,935 --> 00:23:27,702
Next time on Ranma 1/2,
Genma takes a walk.

460
00:23:27,802 --> 00:23:29,835
We'll see you there.

